    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Feature description\n\nWhenever a `redraw` happens anywhere, the non-cleared messages will be resent.\r\n\r\nThis is problematic, if the code that handles messages, also does a redraw. Redraws in my code only happen when any queued messages have not been rendered yet and we're in some sort of blocking call.\r\n\r\nThis would effectively cause some sort of loop.\r\n\r\nTo circumvent this, I currently [wrap any redraw function](https://github.com/folke/noice.nvim/blob/dee23c21c3ff52119d8452b77814e6be75dd23bb/lua/noice/hacks.lua#L55) and when we're inside a redraw cycle, we simply ignore incoming messages.\r\n\r\nNot sure what the best way would be to solve this for `ext_messages`.",
