        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> [<img alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/31730729?s=64&amp;u=9b5f151994618c616e2e1a4ec5d87a5da3113db9&amp;v=4\">@luukvbaal](https://github.com/luukvbaal) this is probably fixed now with your recent changes? Since callbacks can only use fast events?\n\nI was never able to reproduce the loop this issue mentions but that might have been fixed in some of my other PRs avoiding recursion.\nThe \"keep\" message is still cleared/re-emitted which is undesireable for a vim.ui_attach implementation that does not show messages in the same area as the cmdline, but may still be necessary for a GUI that exactly implements the message events (are there any?). I may repurpuse the linked PR at some point if there's something to be done.\n",
